<article id="post-2633" class="post-2633 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-pop-culture category-technology tag-internet">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2010/03/the-end-of-the-individual-experience/" rel="bookmark">The end of the individual experience</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>A few years from now, my kids will be old enough to ask me questions that will require a lot of explanation. Like, for example, what the internet was like when I was their age, how I survived without a mobile data device, did I watch TV in black and white (interestingly enough, I did, but only because the TV was black and white), and what did I name my pet dinosaur (&#8216;cuz, you know, every kid makes that joke of their parents).<br />
One question I also expect them to ask is how I watched TV without having my computer in front of me, firing off notes through Twitter, Facebook, or whatever social media network will be in vogue in 5-8 years from now. I&#8217;ll look at their cute, adorable little faces, and tell them as seriously as I can: There was a time when we watched TV on our own. We went to sporting events in small groups, we went shopping without telling everyone what we were doing, and we could vanish for hours on end without anyone knowing where we were.<br />
The idea that we exist solely as individuals is rapidly becoming extinct.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2010/03/the-end-of-the-individual-experience/#more-2633" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;The end of the individual experience&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2010/03/the-end-of-the-individual-experience/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2010-03-08T15:56:48-07:00">8 March 2010</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/pop-culture/" rel="category tag">Pop Culture</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/technology/" rel="category tag">Technology</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/internet/" rel="tag">internet</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2010/03/the-end-of-the-individual-experience/#respond">Leave a comment<span class="screen-reader-text"> on The end of the individual experience</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
